:Edit
Edit

Use to edit the PostScript source of the current
document or change the properties of the current
page:

PostScript	Displays a window in which you 
		can edit and run PostScript
		source.

Properties	Displays the Page Properties
		window, where you can set page
		size, dpi, page orientation,
		anti-aliasing, job timeout
		value, and method of
		interpretation.

:File
File

Has two options:

Load 	Loads a new file.

Print	Prints the current file.


#####################50##########################
:View
View

Provides ways to navigate multi-page documents:

First Page		Displays the first page.

Last Page		Displays the last page.

Next Page		Displays the next page
			(the default).

Previous Page		Returns to the page
			previously viewed.

Goto Page		Displays a pop up window
			from which you can select
			a specific page for
			viewing.

Reverse Page Order	Reverses the page order
			of the currently
			displayed document.

#####################50##########################
:MainWindowInfo
PageView

This window contains the preview of a PostScript
page. The entire page may not be visible at one
time. Use the mouse to pan around the page.

You can directly manipulate the page with the 
mouse: Press SELECT and drag the pointer to move 
the page. 

ADJUST gives you quick access to any part of the
page: For example, click ADJUST in the upper
left corner of the window to display the upper
left corner of the page.

ADJUST is most useful when the dpi is set to 300 
or more in the Page Properties window. 

#####################50##########################
:SourceDrag
Drag and Drop Target

This box is the place to drop a file icon when 
you want to display it in PageView.

For example, you can press SELECT on an icon 
and drag it from File Manager to PageView. 

When a file is displayed in PageView, you can 
drag the icon from this box to another program
that will accept the file.
  
For example, you can drag from PageView to 
Print Tool to print the file.
 
